    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Isaiah",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 13,
        "summary": "The destruction of Babylon is a type of the destruction at the Second Coming\u2014It will be a day of wrath and vengeance\u2014Babylon (the world) will fall forever\u2014Compare 2\u00a0Nephi 23.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "The burden of Babylon, which Isaiah the son of Amoz did see.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 23:1 (1\u201322).",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 3
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "\u201cBurden\u201d as used in Isaiah is a message of doom \u201clifted up\u201d against a people. Isa. 14:28.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "The historic destruction of wicked Babylon, prophesied in Isa. 13 and 14, is made typical of the ultimate destruction of the whole wicked world. D&C 133:14 (5, 7, 14).",
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 21
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Lift ye up a banner upon the high mountain, exalt the voice unto them, shake the hand, that they may go into the gates of the nobles.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0ensign. TG\u00a0Ensign.",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 19
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 2:2.",
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0raise.",
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 49
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "I have commanded my sanctified ones, I have also called my mighty ones for mine anger, even them that rejoice in my highness.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "\u201cSanctified ones\u201d and \u201csaints\u201d are synonymously translated from either of two Hebrew words in the Old Testament.",
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 35
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Joel 3:11.",
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 65
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 87,
                        "end": 91
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The noise of a multitude in the mountains, like as of a great people; a tumultuous noise of the kingdoms of nations gathered together: the Lord of hosts mustereth the host of the battle.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Zeph. 3:8.",
                        "start": 96,
                        "end": 104
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0War.",
                        "start": 179,
                        "end": 185
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "They come from a far country, from the end of heaven, even the Lord, and the weapons of his indignation, to destroy the whole land.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Zech. 12:9 (4, 8\u20139).",
                        "start": 108,
                        "end": 115
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 58
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Howl ye; for the day of the Lord is at hand; it shall come as a destruction from the Almighty.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 14:31.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 4
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Day of the Lord.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 20
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 35
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore shall all hands be faint, and every man's heart shall melt:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 7:66.",
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 68
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And they shall be afraid: pangs and sorrows shall take hold of them; they shall be in pain as a woman that travaileth: they shall be amazed one at another; their faces shall be as flames.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Pain.",
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 90
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hosea 13:13.",
                        "start": 107,
                        "end": 117
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 168,
                        "end": 179
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Behold, the day of the Lord cometh, cruel both with wrath and fierce anger, to lay the land desolate: and he shall destroy the sinners thereof out of it.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Earth, Cleansing of; World, End of.",
                        "start": 115,
                        "end": 122
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For the stars of heaven and the constellations thereof shall not give their light: the sun shall be darkened in his going forth, and the moon shall not cause her light to shine.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ezek. 32:7 (7\u20138); Joel 2:10; Matt. 24:29.",
                        "start": 100,
                        "end": 108
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And I will punish the world for their evil, and the wicked for their iniquity; and I will cause the arrogancy of the proud to cease, and will lay low the haughtiness of the terrible.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Punish.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 17
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0World.",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 27
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Haughtiness.",
                        "start": 154,
                        "end": 165
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0tyrants.",
                        "start": 173,
                        "end": 181
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 37
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "I will make a man more precious than fine gold; even a man than the golden wedge of Ophir.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 24:6. TG\u00a0Worth of Souls.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Job 28:16.",
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 74
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore I will shake the heavens, and the earth shall remove out of her place, in the wrath of the Lord of hosts, and in the day of his fierce anger.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hag. 2:6; 2\u00a0Ne. 8:6; 3\u00a0Ne. 26:3.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 22
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 14:26 (22\u201326); 24:1; D&C 88:87 (87\u201392).",
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 49
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Earth, Renewal of.",
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 62
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Lam. 1:12.",
                        "start": 145,
                        "end": 150
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And it shall be as the chased roe, and as a sheep that no man taketh up: they shall every man turn to his own people, and flee every one into his own land.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0hunted deer.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 33
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0none gathers in.",
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 71
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 50:16.",
                        "start": 110,
                        "end": 116
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Lands of Inheritance.",
                        "start": 150,
                        "end": 154
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Every one that is found shall be thrust through; and every one that is joined unto them shall fall by the sword.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0pierced or stabbed.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 39
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 78,
                        "end": 87
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Their children also shall be dashed to pieces before their eyes; their houses shall be spoiled, and their wives ravished.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Nahum 3:10.",
                        "start": 6,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Zech. 14:2 (1\u20132).",
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 77
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0plundered.",
                        "start": 87,
                        "end": 94
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Behold, I will stir up the Medes against them, which shall not regard silver; and as for gold, they shall not delight in it.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Dan. 5:30\u201331.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 32
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 82,
                        "end": 88
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Their bows also shall dash the young men to pieces; and they shall have no pity on the fruit of the womb; their eye shall not spare children.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And Babylon, the glory of kingdoms, the beauty of the Chaldees' excellency, shall be as when God overthrew Sodom and Gomorrah.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Babylon.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 11
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0vainglorious grandeur of the Babylonians.",
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 46
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 23:13.",
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 63
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 20:16; Amos 4:11.",
                        "start": 97,
                        "end": 106
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 19:24; Jer. 50:40.",
                        "start": 107,
                        "end": 112
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "It shall never be inhabited, neither shall it be dwelt in from generation to generation: neither shall the Arabian pitch tent there; neither shall the shepherds make their fold there.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 50:3.",
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 27
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But wild beasts of the desert shall lie there; and their houses shall be full of doleful creatures; and owls shall dwell there, and satyrs shall dance there.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 34:14 (11\u201315).",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0he-goats, or demons.",
                        "start": 132,
                        "end": 138
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the wild beasts of the islands shall cry in their desolate houses, and dragons in their pleasant palaces: and her time is near to come, and her days shall not be prolonged.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0palaces.",
                        "start": 63,
                        "end": 69
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0(perhaps) jackals, or wild dogs.",
                        "start": 75,
                        "end": 82
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 91
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 123,
                        "end": 125
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}